The paper focuses on the application of graph neural networks in robotics for predicting the effects of actions on groups of articulated objects. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for learning and prediction also suggests the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the framework for partially observable environments, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
